<h2>How Ipamorelin Works: The GHSR-1a Pathway</h2>

<p>Ipamorelin mimics ghrelin, the body's natural hunger hormone. But unlike ghrelin itself, ipamorelin binds to only one specific receptor subtype: the growth hormone secretagogue receptor 1a (GHSR-1a), located in the pituitary gland and hypothalamus.</p>

<p>This selective binding is the key to its clean effect profile. It triggers GH release without activating the pathways responsible for cortisol, prolactin, or appetite stimulation.</p>

